    scripture: "Call unto me, and I will answer thee, and shew thee great and mighty things, which thou knowest not.",
    walk: `I know what's playing in your head right now. It's not a thought — it's a loop. You need it. When are you going to get it? You need it. Over and over, like a song you can't shut off. I know, because that same loop played in my head.

Here's the first honest thing I'm going to tell you, and I promise to be honest with you for all thirty of these days: the loop doesn't mean you're weak, and it doesn't mean you don't really want to quit. You're here because you truly want to climb out of this hell — nobody handed you this book by court order. That wanting? Hold onto it. Because the loop is going to tell you the wanting isn't real. It is.

Right now you might not have words to pray. You might not even be sure God is listening — I get that more than you know, because I didn't believe in God at all when my fight started. But this verse says something wild: Call unto me, and I will answer thee. That's God's phone number. You don't need the right words. You don't need to be clean first. You don't need to believe hard enough. You just dial.

Today, the only job you have is this: when the loop plays — and it will play — you answer it with a call of your own. Even if all you can get out is "God, help me." That counts. That's the whole prayer. He hears it, and He answers. I'm living proof.`,
