    title: "Are You Sure?",
    ref: "Philippians 2:13",
    scripture: "For it is God which worketh in you both to will and to do of his good pleasure.",
    walk: `By now the loop has changed its tune. Yesterday it was "you need it, when are you going to get it." Today the mind gets sneakier. It starts asking questions. Are you sure you want to do this? Do you really know what's coming? Do you know how bad this is going to get?

I'm not going to lie to you — I told you I'd be honest. The mind is asking that question because it knows the pain hasn't fully arrived yet. The bones are just starting to whisper. And the enemy wants you to quit the fight before the hardest part, because he knows something you need to know too: if you make it through what's coming, you come out the other side a different person.

But here's what I want you to see today, and it's right there in the verse: that desire in you to be free — the wanting that brought you to Day 2 — you didn't manufacture that. "It is God which worketh in you both to will and to do." The will itself is His work. Before you ever prayed, before you ever believed, God was already in you, building the want. So when the mind asks "are you sure?" — the answer isn't found in your confidence. I had none. The answer is: God started this, and what He starts, He finishes.

So yes — it's going to get harder before it gets easier. I won't hide that from you, because you'd find out anyway and then you'd stop trusting me. But you are not walking toward that pain alone, and you are not walking toward it on your own strength. You're walking with the One who put the fight in you in the first place.`,
    prayer: `God, my mind keeps asking if I'm sure. I'm scared of what's coming. But You put this wanting in me — I didn't make it myself. So finish what You started, Lord. I'm not turning back today. Amen.`,
